Do Not Take Driving Lessons for Granted: Passing Rate in WA Declining

cars
/u/adam VP
follow
Published on 2020-03-26 22:26:29
2 min read



The passing rate for driver’s license has been steadily decreasing in Western Australia for the past ten years. The trend is also applicable in some Australian states, as well.

 

According to the report by ABC, the passing rate has gone down from the 56% in 2010 to only 43% in 2019. Some areas around Perth have even worse pass rates than the average. For example, Willagee, Joondalup, and Mirrabooka only have a 64% failure rate.

 

Instead of taking driving schools EzLicence seriously, some students and first-time learners try to look for centers around the country that are supposedly lax with the rules. They hear stories from friends and acquaintances about areas where they will have a higher likelihood of passing the assessment.

 

This, of course, that is not the right attitude to have.

 

Taking lessons from legitimate driving schools will increase your chances of passing the driver’s license test for the first time. It is not, at all, easy to do. In fact, second-takers are much more common than you think. It is not even rare for some people to take the test and fail for fourth, fifth, and sixth times.

 

What You Will Learn from Driving Schools

 

  1. Proper techniques -- First-time learners are easier to teach because they have not yet developed bad habits. Experienced drivers from other countries, for instance, will have to unlearn some of the practices they have been used to and learn new techniques to pass the assessment.

 

  1. What to expect -- The best thing about driving schools such as EzLicence is that they will mimic the scenario of the driving assessment test, especially during the practical exam part. They will also equip you with the right knowledge on regulatory signs and road markings during the instruction phase. As a result, nothing in the driver’s license test will surprise you anymore.

 

  1. Be comfortable -- Students tend to make mistakes due to anxiety and stress. What the driving lessons will teach you is how to be more comfortable behind the wheel. Comfort will only come if you have the right skills and experience. With hours of lessons, you will gain both.

 

  1. Discipline -- The common reason why students fail the driving test is the lack of patience. They tend to move fast when they should slow down. They fail to act quickly when they should. They fail to spot the regulatory sign and maneuver at the right time. They did not position themselves correctly before making a maneuver. These little details might be monotonous and even boring, but they are required for you to develop good habits. It is crucial since you are not only responsible for your personal safety, but those of your passengers and the other motorists, as well.

 

  1. How to anticipate risks -- When you are out on the road, you place yourself at risk. However, you can lower the danger if you develop the right foundation. As you gain experience on the road, you will learn how to anticipate the threats. For example, you can foresee what the other motorists will do based on their driving patterns. You can quickly employ counter-maneuvers to ensure your safety.

 

Finally, you will develop self-confidence when you enroll in driving schools. When you know how to correctly maneuver or position yourself while behind the wheel, you will make a move with confidence.
